Subject: [PATCH 10/20] media: cedrus: vc1: fix the MVMODE hardware code
 mapping

vc1_mvmode_map translates the motion-vector mode to the hardware PICMV
MVMODE code. It was set to {3, 2, 0, 1}, which is the vendor library's
mMVModeTable literal -- but that table is indexed by the vendor's mv mode
enum order (1MV-halfpel-bilinear, 1MV-halfpel, 1MV, mixed), whereas this
driver indexes it with the ffmpeg/uAPI enum order (1MV-halfpel-bilinear,
1MV, 1MV-halfpel, mixed). Copying the literal therefore swapped the codes
for 1MV and 1MV-halfpel.

Pictures using 1MV or 1MV-halfpel motion mode (e.g. progressive/main P
frames, and interlaced-frame P/B frames which the hardware codes as 1MV)
were programmed with the wrong mode and decoded with accumulating drift.
Streams that only use 1MV-halfpel-bilinear or mixed motion modes were
unaffected, since those two entries are identical in both orderings.

Use the correct mapping {3, 0, 2, 1}: 1MV_HPEL_BILIN -> 3, 1MV -> 0,
1MV_HPEL -> 2, MIXED_MV -> 1. With this, progressive content using
1MV-halfpel (e.g. vc1/Robotica_720.wmv) and interlaced-frame content
(vc1-samples/ilaced_twomv.vc1) decode bit-exact against the software
decoder.

